               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390408-name-1504" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1504" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1504" type="surname" value="ROWLAND"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1504" type="given" value="OWEN"></interp>OWEN ROWLAND</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a porter. On the 2nd of April I was in Greenwich fair—I felt a tug at my right-hand pocket, and missed my handkerchief from it—I saw the prisoner walking away from me, and looking confused—I took hold of him, and said, "I believe you have my handkerchief"—he said he had not—I began to search him—he would not allow me to do so—the policeman came up and found the handkerchief between his legs in his trowsers.</p>
               <p>
